One of the following methods may be used to grant an app access to a custom device:                 - an interface class may define access policy for either allowing unrestricted access or access restricted to a specific capability                 - a device interface instance may grant access to apps based on well-known or custom capabilities                 - (Deprecated) Privileged App Support: device metadata may grant access to specific PFNs associated to device container's PnP state                 Note: custom capabilities are typically the correct way to enable an app to access a custom device.
